A Johannesburg motorist has been charged with culpable homicide after she fatally knocked down a female metro police department officer on Saturday. The 37-year-old traffic warden and her colleagues were at an accident scene on the N12, between the Golden Highway and the K43 when the suspected drunk driver drove into her. JMPD spokesperson, Xolani Fihla says the driver didn't stop, and fled the scene. Officers then gave chase and arrested the suspect.